<subSubSection id="C35CC1F7D843FFDDFF253BB3FE6FFA1D" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF9927CD843FFDDFF253BB3FE6FFA1D" blockId="4.[140,1108,554,1672]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="B9324E6ED843FFDDFF253BB3FE58FB81" bold="true" box="[185,453,1011,1037]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="B9324E6ED843FFDDFF253BB3FEDAFB81" box="[185,327,1011,1037]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" reason="1">Description</emphasis>
of female.
</emphasis>
Body length: 5.4 mm (n=1), wing length: 4.1 mm (n=1). Differs from the male redescription provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD7EF8DD843FFDDFD383C57FCD1FBBE" author="Arnaud PH Jr." box="[676,844,1047,1074]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" pagination="1 - 18" refId="ref4794" refString="Arnaud PH Jr. (1963) A revision of the genus Borgmeiermyia Townsend (Diptera, Tachinidae). American Museum Novitates 2133, 1 - 18." type="journal article" year="1963">Arnaud (1963)</bibRefCitation>
by the following: Frons at vertex level about 0.35 of head width; frons at most four times width of parafrons (at narrowest point, beside ocellar triangle); parafacialia narrowing slightly below (not strongly as male); antenna not multifissicorn and yellow, but brown at extreme base and apical fourth of arista and posterior portion of flagellomere; flagellomere elongate, reaching level of vibrissa; gena about one-sixth of eye height. Length of median lateral scutellar seta about 1/2 or slightly longer than 1/2 of the posterior lateral scutellar seta (the male 
<typeStatus id="54FD2CDED843FFDDFE9C3D4DFEFEFAAB" box="[256,355,1293,1319]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">holotype</typeStatus>
between 1/2 and 3/5). Both female specimen and the male 
<typeStatus id="54FD2CDED843FFDDFB8B3D4DFF21FAC7" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">holotype</typeStatus>
have R 
<subScript id="17C29039D843FFDDFE883D03FEB3FADD" attach="left" box="[276,302,1347,1361]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">4+5</subScript>
setulose dorsally on the whole distance to the r-m crossvein, although the male of 
<collectingRegion id="49825C9ED843FFDDFE8F3D14FE26FAE1" box="[275,443,1363,1390]" country="Brazil" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
(examined by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD7EF8DD843FFDDFDFF3D13FC9EFAE2" author="Arnaud PH Jr." box="[611,771,1363,1390]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" pagination="1 - 18" refId="ref4794" refString="Arnaud PH Jr. (1963) A revision of the genus Borgmeiermyia Townsend (Diptera, Tachinidae). American Museum Novitates 2133, 1 - 18." type="journal article" year="1963">Arnaud, 1963</bibRefCitation>
) was characterized as setulose at only half the distance to r-m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
